# Production Environment Variables for My-Love PWA
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE showing required environment variables for production builds.
# The actual .env.production file (containing your values) is gitignored for security.
#
# ============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this template to create your production environment file:
#    cp .env.production.example .env.production
#
# 2. Edit .env.production and replace placeholder values with your relationship data
#
# 3. Build the production bundle (values are injected at build time):
#    npm run build
#
# 4. Deploy the generated dist/ folder to GitHub Pages or your hosting service:
#    npm run deploy
#
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# ✅ .env.production is already listed in .gitignore
# ✅ Never commit .env.production to version control
# ✅ These are NOT secrets - values are embedded in the public JavaScript bundle
# ✅ They are personal relationship data for single-user PWA deployment
# ✅ Anyone with access to your deployed app can inspect these values in DevTools
#
# If you need to keep relationship data truly private, consider:
# - Deploying to a private server with authentication
# - Using environment variables on your hosting platform instead of committing them
#
# ============================================================================
# HOW IT WORKS
# ============================================================================
#
# Vite injects environment variables at BUILD TIME (not runtime):
# - Variables prefixed with VITE_ are accessible via import.meta.env in source code
# - During `vite build`, these values are replaced with string literals in the bundle
# - The APP_CONFIG object (src/config/constants.ts) exposes these values to the app
# - At runtime, the app checks APP_CONFIG.isPreConfigured to determine if values are present
#
# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# ============================================================================

# VITE_PARTNER_NAME
# ==================
# Partner's name displayed throughout the app in messages and UI
#
# Format: Any string (recommended: First name or nickname)
# Example: VITE_PARTNER_NAME=Sarah
# Example: VITE_PARTNER_NAME=My Love
#
# Used in:
# - Daily love messages
# - Settings display
# - Relationship duration counter label
#
VITE_PARTNER_NAME=YourPartnerName

# VITE_RELATIONSHIP_START_DATE
# ==============================
# Relationship start date used to calculate relationship duration counter
#
# Format: ISO 8601 date string (YYYY-MM-DD)
# Example: VITE_RELATIONSHIP_START_DATE=2024-01-15
# Example: VITE_RELATIONSHIP_START_DATE=2025-10-18
#
# Validation Rules:
# - Must be a valid date in YYYY-MM-DD format
# - Should be in the past (future dates may cause negative duration)
# - No time component required (assumes midnight UTC)
#
# Used in:
# - Relationship duration counter calculation
# - Anniversary detection
# - Settings display
#
VITE_RELATIONSHIP_START_DATE=YYYY-MM-DD

# ============================================================================
# TESTING YOUR CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
#
# After creating .env.production and running `npm run build`:
#
# 1. Check that dist/ folder was created successfully
#
# 2. Verify environment variables were injected into the bundle:
#    grep -r "YourPartnerName" dist/assets/*.js
#    (Should find your partner name in the bundled JavaScript)
#
# 3. Run smoke tests (automatically runs during `npm run deploy`):
#    node scripts/smoke-tests.js
#
# 4. Test locally with production build:
#    npm run preview
#    Open http://localhost:4173/My-Love/
#    Verify partner name and relationship duration display correctly
#
# 5. Deploy and verify on live site:
#    npm run deploy
#    Open https://yourusername.github.io/My-Love/
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# Partner name not showing in deployed app:
# - Verify .env.production exists in project root (not in dist/ or src/)
# - Verify variable names are spelled correctly (case-sensitive)
# - Verify you ran `npm run build` AFTER creating .env.production
# - Check browser DevTools console for APP_CONFIG warnings
#
# Relationship duration showing "NaN" or incorrect value:
# - Verify date format is exactly YYYY-MM-DD
# - Verify date is valid (e.g., not 2024-02-30)
# - Verify date is in the past
#
# Changes not appearing after editing .env.production:
# - You must rebuild: `npm run build` (build-time injection, not runtime)
# - Clear browser cache or open in incognito mode
# - Verify service worker updated (DevTools → Application → Service Workers)
#
# ============================================================================
